KZLEKS
Over the past 10 years, I have changed a dozen different professions and places of work. For the most part, I worked in the service industry. At the same time, I managed my musical project and spent everything I earned on its development. Back then I had a total of hundreds of thousands of plays. Then I found myself on another continent, after many trials I returned home and got a job as a product manager in a team that writes open source applications.

KZLEKS
In February, I worked on evenor, an application for storing notes and media files that runs on technology that I initially did not understand without any technical background. Worked on product positioning - looking for competitors, organizing documentation and asking questions to narrow down the target audience. I helped write the NLNet grant proposal, and some of what I wrote is still on the team's website.

